Wash and dry produce.

Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Drain @pineapple{4%ounce} over a #small bowl{}, reserving
juice. Pat pineapple dry with #paper towels{}.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for
4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and
reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, dice @roma tomato{1}(diced). Halve, peel, and thinly slice
@yellow onion{1}(thinly sliced); mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP
for 4 servings). Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(roughly chopped). Halve, core,
and thinly slice @long green pepper{1}(thinly sliced) into strips.

In a second small bowl, combine tomato, minced onion, half the cilantro, and a
big squeeze of lime juice to taste. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large, dry #pan over medium-high heat. Add pineapple; cook, stirring
occasionally, until lightly charred, ~{3-5%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add
sliced onion and green pepper; cook, stirring occasionally, until charred and
softened, ~{7-9%minutes}.

Add half the @fajita spice blend{1%tbsp} and a splash of water; cook, stirring,
until fragrant and water has evaporated, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and
pepper. Turn off heat; transfer to plate with pineapple. Wipe out pan.

> TIP: Tent with foil to keep warm.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Once pan is hot, add
@ground pork{10%ounce}; cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and
cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add @chili powder{1%tsp}, remaining fajita spice, reserved pineapple juice, and
a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Cook, stirring, until pork is coated and sauce has
reduced, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from heat and stir in a big squeeze of lime
juice.

In a third small bowl, combine @sour cream{4%tbsp} and @hot sauce{1%tsp} to taste.
Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season
with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork; stir in lime zest, remaining cilantro, and
@butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between bowls; top with pork, pineapple and veggies, and pico de
gallo. Sprinkle with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}. Drizzle with spicy crema.
Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.